#Univariate

#Age-group
df_age = 
  lung_cohort %>%
  select(Sex, Age) %>%
  group_by(Sex, Age)
ggplot(df_age, aes(x = Age, fill=Sex, color = Sex)) + 
  geom_histogram(position = "identity", alpha = 0.5)

#Gender-pie chart
df_sex = data.frame(
  group = c("Male", "Female"),
  value = c(60.5, 39.5)
  )
df_sex = df_sex %>%
  arrange(desc(group)) %>%
  mutate(prop = value / sum(df_sex$value)*100) %>%
  mutate(ypos = cumsum(prop)- 0.5*prop)
pie_sex = 
  ggplot(df_sex, aes(x="", y=prop, fill=group)) + 
  geom_bar(width = 1, stat = "identity", color="white") + 
  coord_polar("y", start=0) +
  theme_void() +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette="Set2") +
  geom_text(aes(y = ypos, label = group), color = "white", size=6)
pie_sex

#ECOG-pie chart
df_ecog <- data.frame(
  group = c("0", "1", "2", "3", "missing"),
  value = c(27.632, 49.561, 21.930, 0.439, 0.439)
  )
df_ecog = df_ecog %>%
  arrange(desc(group)) %>%
  mutate(prop = value / sum(df_sex$value)*100) %>%
  mutate(ypos = cumsum(prop)- 0.5*prop)
pie_ecog = 
  ggplot(df_ecog, aes(x="", y=value, fill=group)) + 
  geom_bar(width = 1, stat = "identity") + 
  coord_polar("y", start=0) +
  theme_void() +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette="Set2") +
  geom_text(aes(y = ypos, label = group), color = "white", size=6)
pie_ecog

# histogram by Karno
df_karno = 
  pivot_longer(
    lung_cohort,
    KarnoPH:KarnoPAT,
    names_to = "karno",
    names_prefix = "Karno",
    values_to = "Score"
  )
